athematics and can be formulated as follows: Every simple finite dimensional simple Lie algebra over an algebraically closed field of characteristic p › 3 is of classical, Cartan, or Melikian type. This is the second part of a three-volume book about the classification of the simple Lie algebras over algebraically closed fields of characteristic › 3. The first volume contains the methods, examples and a first classification result. This second volume presents insight in the structure of tori of Hamiltonian and Melikian algebras. Based on sandwich element methods due to A. I. Kostrikin and A. A. Premet and the investigations of filtered and graded Lie algebras, a complete proof for the classification of absolute toral rank 2 simple Lie algebras over algebraically closed fields of characteristic › 3 is given. Contents Tori in Hamiltonian and Melikian algebras1-sectionsSandwich elements and rigid toriTowards graded algebrasThe toral rank 2 case  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aLie algebras. 7aMATHEMATICS / Algebra / Abstract.2bisacsh  aLie algebras, fields of positive characteristic, classification.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Expositions in Mathematics Backlist eBook Packagez978311049496908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2017z978311071954308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2017z9783110540550oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE ENGLISH 2017z978311062526408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Mathematics 2017z9783110548204oZDB-23-DMA0 cEPUBz97831105168900 cprintz978311051676040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311051760640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110517606423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9783110517606.jpg  a97